Problem: Rising Temperature
Description

Table: Weather

Column Name	Type
id	int
recordDate	date
temperature	int
id is unique
No two rows share the same recordDate
Each row records the temperature for a specific day

 Objective

Find all id values where the temperature is higher than the previous day (yesterday).

Return the result in any order.

Approach
Compare each day with its previous day
Use a self join on the Weather table
Match rows where the date difference is exactly 1 day
Filter where today's temperature is greater than yesterday’s

SQL Solution

SELECT w1.id
FROM Weather w1
JOIN Weather w2
ON DATEDIFF(w1.recordDate, w2.recordDate) = 1
WHERE w1.temperature > w2.temperature;

Alternative (Using DATE_SUB)

SELECT w1.id
FROM Weather w1
JOIN Weather w2
ON w2.recordDate = DATE_SUB(w1.recordDate, INTERVAL 1 DAY)
WHERE w1.temperature > w2.temperature;
